<script>
/**
* jQuery Plugin: Sticky Tabs
*
* @author Aidan Lister <aidan@php.net>
* adapted by Ruben Arslan to activate parent tabs too
* http://www.aidanlister.com/2014/03/persisting-the-tab-state-in-bootstrap/
*/
(function($) {
"use strict";
$.fn.rmarkdownStickyTabs = function() {
var context = this;
// Show the tab corresponding with the hash in the URL, or the first tab
var showStuffFromHash = function() {
var hash = window.location.hash;
var selector = hash ? 'a[href="' + hash + '"]' : 'li.active > a';
var $selector = $(selector, context);
if($selector.data('toggle') === "tab") {
$selector.tab('show');
// walk up the ancestors of this element, show any hidden tabs
$selector.parents('.section.tabset').each(function(i, elm) {
var link = $('a[href="#' + $(elm).attr('id') + '"]');
if(link.data('toggle') === "tab") {
link.tab("show");
}
});
}
};
// Set the correct tab when the page loads
showStuffFromHash(context);
// Set the correct tab when a user uses their back/forward button
$(window).on('hashchange', function() {
showStuffFromHash(context);
});
// Change the URL when tabs are clicked
$('a', context).on('click', function(e) {
history.pushState(null, null, this.href);
showStuffFromHash(context);
});
return this;
};
}(jQuery));
window.buildTabsets = function(tocID) {
// build a tabset from a section div with the .tabset class
function buildTabset(tabset) {
// check for fade and pills options
var fade = tabset.hasClass("tabset-fade");
var pills = tabset.hasClass("tabset-pills");
var navClass = pills ? "nav-pills" : "nav-tabs";
// determine the heading level of the tabset and tabs
var match = tabset.attr('class').match(/level(\d) /);
if (match === null)
return;
var tabsetLevel = Number(match[1]);
var tabLevel = tabsetLevel + 1;
// find all subheadings immediately below
var tabs = tabset.find("div.section.level" + tabLevel);
if (!tabs.length)
return;
// create tablist and tab-content elements
var tabList = $('<ul class="nav ' + navClass + '" role="tablist"></ul>');
$(tabs[0]).before(tabList);
var tabContent = $('<div class="tab-content"></div>');
$(tabs[0]).before(tabContent);
// build the tabset
var activeTab = 0;
tabs.each(function(i) {
// get the tab div
var tab = $(tabs[i]);
// get the id then sanitize it for use with bootstrap tabs
var id = tab.attr('id');
// see if this is marked as the active tab
if (tab.hasClass('active'))
activeTab = i;
// remove any table of contents entries associated with
// this ID (since we'll be removing the heading element)
$("div#" + tocID + " li a[href='#" + id + "']").parent().remove();
// sanitize the id for use with bootstrap tabs
id = id.replace(/[.\/?&!#<>]/g, '').replace(/\s/g, '_');
tab.attr('id', id);
// get the heading element within it, grab it's text, then remove it
var heading = tab.find('h' + tabLevel + ':first');
var headingText = heading.html();
heading.remove();
// build and append the tab list item
var a = $('<a role="tab" data-toggle="tab">' + headingText + '</a>');
a.attr('href', '#' + id);
a.attr('aria-controls', id);
var li = $('<li role="presentation"></li>');
li.append(a);
tabList.append(li);
// set it's attributes
tab.attr('role', 'tabpanel');
tab.addClass('tab-pane');
tab.addClass('tabbed-pane');
if (fade)
tab.addClass('fade');
// move it into the tab content div
tab.detach().appendTo(tabContent);
});
// set active tab
$(tabList.children('li')[activeTab]).addClass('active');
var active = $(tabContent.children('div.section')[activeTab]);
active.addClass('active');
if (fade)
active.addClass('in');
if (tabset.hasClass("tabset-sticky"))
tabset.rmarkdownStickyTabs();
}
// convert section divs with the .tabset class to tabsets
var tabsets = $("div.section.tabset");
tabsets.each(function(i) {
buildTabset($(tabsets[i]));
});
};
</script>

<div class="container-fluid main-container">
<div class="fluid-row" id="header">
<h1 class="title toc-ignore">BKM Assignment</h1>
</div>
<p>This document is an analysis of BKM data for the periods of January 2019 to June 2019. Data can be reached from <a href="https://bkm.com.tr/" class="uri">https://bkm.com.tr/</a></p>
<div id="importing-the-libraries" class="section level3">
<h3>Importing the Libraries</h3>
<p>Firstly, we have to import libraries that we will use throughout the analysis.</p>
<pre class="r"><code class="hljs"><span class="hljs-keyword">library</span>(rvest)
<span class="hljs-keyword">library</span>(dplyr)
<span class="hljs-keyword">library</span>(ggplot2)</code></pre>
</div>
<div id="importing-the-data" class="section level3">
<h3>Importing the Data</h3>
<p>The file is downloaded from the link and is assigned to a new variable called ‚Äútable‚Äù.</p>
<pre class="r"><code class="hljs">url &lt;- <span class="hljs-string">"https://bkm.com.tr/secilen-aya-ait-sektorel-gelisim/?filter_year=2019&amp;filter_month=1"</span>
page &lt;- read_html(url)
table &lt;- html_table(page, fill = <span class="hljs-literal">TRUE</span>)[[<span class="hljs-number">4</span>]][-c(<span class="hljs-number">1</span>:<span class="hljs-number">2</span>),]
<span class="hljs-keyword">for</span>(i <span class="hljs-keyword">in</span> <span class="hljs-number">2</span>:<span class="hljs-number">6</span>) {
url &lt;- paste(<span class="hljs-string">"https://bkm.com.tr/secilen-aya-ait-sektorel-gelisim/?filter_year=2019&amp;filter_month="</span>, i, sep = <span class="hljs-string">""</span>)
page &lt;- read_html(url)
table &lt;- bind_rows(table, html_table(page, fill = <span class="hljs-literal">TRUE</span>)[[<span class="hljs-number">4</span>]][-c(<span class="hljs-number">1</span>:<span class="hljs-number">2</span>),-<span class="hljs-number">1</span>])
}
temp1 &lt;- c(table%&gt;% select(X1) %&gt;% filter(X1 != <span class="hljs-string">"NA"</span>))
temp2 &lt;- c(rep(temp1[[<span class="hljs-string">"X1"</span>]], times=<span class="hljs-number">6</span>))
temp3 &lt;- as.character(c(rep(seq(<span class="hljs-number">1</span>:<span class="hljs-number">26</span>), times=<span class="hljs-number">6</span>)))
tmpTable &lt;- table %&gt;% mutate(X1 = temp2) %&gt;% filter(X1 != <span class="hljs-string">"TOPLAM"</span>) %&gt;% mutate(X6=temp3)
month_1 &lt;- c(rep(<span class="hljs-number">1</span>:<span class="hljs-number">6</span>, times=<span class="hljs-number">1</span>, each=<span class="hljs-number">26</span>))
table &lt;- tmpTable %&gt;% mutate(month = month_1)
table2 &lt;- as.data.frame(lapply(table, <span class="hljs-keyword">function</span>(x) as.numeric(gsub(<span class="hljs-string">","</span>, <span class="hljs-string">"."</span>, gsub(<span class="hljs-string">"\\."</span>, <span class="hljs-string">""</span>, x)))))
table2[,<span class="hljs-number">1</span>] &lt;- tmpTable[,<span class="hljs-number">1</span>]
table2[,<span class="hljs-number">6</span>] &lt;- tmpTable[,<span class="hljs-number">6</span>]
table &lt;- table2
names(table) &lt;- c(<span class="hljs-string">"Sector"</span>, <span class="hljs-string">"TransactionCount_CC"</span>, <span class="hljs-string">"TransactionCount_DC"</span>, <span class="hljs-string">"TransactionAmount_CC"</span>, <span class="hljs-string">"TransactionAmount_DC"</span>, <span class="hljs-string">"Sector_ID"</span>, <span class="hljs-string">"Month"</span>)</code></pre>
<p>Now let‚Äôs have a look at the beginning and end of the variable ‚Äútable‚Äù.</p>

<div id="analyses-related-to-the-data" class="section level3">
<h3>Analyses Related to the Data</h3>
<ul>
<li>The first thing is to find the sectors with the highest transaction amount for both debit and credit cards.</li>
<li>We can see that the sectors ‚ÄúMARKET VE ALI≈ûVERƒ∞≈û MERKEZLERƒ∞ (Sector ID=17)‚Äù, ‚ÄúGƒ∞Yƒ∞M VE AKSESUAR (Sector ID=9)‚Äù, ‚ÄúBENZƒ∞N VE YAKIT ƒ∞STASYONLARI (Sector ID=3)‚Äù, ‚Äú√áE≈ûƒ∞TLƒ∞ GIDA (Sector ID=5)‚Äù, ‚ÄúHƒ∞ZMET SEKT√ñRLERƒ∞ (Sector ID=11)‚Äù, ‚ÄúYEMEK (Sector ID=25)‚Äù, ‚ÄúELEKTRƒ∞K-ELEKTRONƒ∞K E≈ûYA, Bƒ∞LGƒ∞SAYAR (Sector ID=8)‚Äù are the ones with the highest. So we can group the rest as ‚ÄúOTHER‚Äù.</li>
<li>We can now find the fraction of the sum of transaction amounts for each sectors.</li>
<li>Then we can visualise them in a pie chart.</li>
<li>We can conclude that the sector of ‚ÄúMARKET VE ALI≈ûVERƒ∞≈û MERKEZLERƒ∞‚Äù has a grave share with respect to the rest of the sector.</li>
</ul>
<pre class="r"><code class="hljs">table %&gt;%
filter (Month == <span class="hljs-number">6</span>) %&gt;%
transmute(Sector, Sector_ID, Tot_Tran_Amount = (TransactionAmount_CC + TransactionAmount_DC)) %&gt;%
arrange(desc(Tot_Tran_Amount)) %&gt;%
mutate(Sector_ID = case_when(Sector_ID %<span class="hljs-keyword">in</span>% c(<span class="hljs-string">"17"</span>,<span class="hljs-string">"9"</span>,<span class="hljs-string">"3"</span>,<span class="hljs-string">"5"</span>,<span class="hljs-string">"11"</span>,<span class="hljs-string">"25"</span>,<span class="hljs-string">"8"</span>) ~ Sector_ID, <span class="hljs-literal">TRUE</span> ~ <span class="hljs-string">"99"</span>)) %&gt;%
group_by(Sector_ID) %&gt;%
summarise(Tot_Tran_Amount = sum(Tot_Tran_Amount)) %&gt;%
mutate(Fra_Tran_Amount = round(Tot_Tran_Amount / sum(Tot_Tran_Amount)*<span class="hljs-number">100</span>,<span class="hljs-number">2</span>)) %&gt;%
ggplot(data = ., aes(x = <span class="hljs-string">""</span>, y = Fra_Tran_Amount, fill = Sector_ID)) +
geom_bar(width = <span class="hljs-number">1</span>, stat = <span class="hljs-string">"identity"</span>, color = <span class="hljs-string">"black"</span>) +
coord_polar(<span class="hljs-string">"y"</span>, start = <span class="hljs-number">0</span>)+
geom_text(aes(x = <span class="hljs-string">""</span>, y = Fra_Tran_Amount, label = Fra_Tran_Amount),position = position_stack(vjust = <span class="hljs-number">0.5</span>),color = <span class="hljs-string">"black"</span>)+
labs(fill = <span class="hljs-string">"Sectors"</span>)+
theme_void()</code></pre>

<p>Let‚Äôs now compare and see if there is a relation between ARABA Kƒ∞RALAMA (Sector ID = 1) and ARA√á Kƒ∞RALAMA-SATI≈û/SERVƒ∞S/YEDEK PAR√áA (Sector ID = 2) with a line plot. There is no obvious visual relation between those two sectors.</p>
<pre class="r"><code class="hljs">table %&gt;%
filter (Sector_ID %<span class="hljs-keyword">in</span>% c(<span class="hljs-string">"1"</span>, <span class="hljs-string">"2"</span>)) %&gt;%
mutate(Tot_Tran_Count = (TransactionCount_CC + TransactionCount_DC)) %&gt;%
ggplot(data=., aes(x=Month, y=Tot_Tran_Count, group=Sector)) +
geom_line(aes(color=Sector))+
geom_point(aes(color=Sector))</code></pre>
